Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Permission Denied Error
Problem: Cannot capture packets due to permission issues

Solution:

# Ensure user is in wireshark group
groups $USER

# If not in wireshark group, add user
sudo usermod -a -G wireshark $USER

# Log out and log back in, or use:
newgrp wireshark
Issue 2: No Interfaces Available
Problem: Wireshark shows no network interfaces

Solution:

# Check if interfaces exist
ip link show

# Restart network manager
sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager

# Check dumpcap permissions
ls -la /usr/bin/dumpcap
Issue 3: Capture File Too Large
Problem: Capture file becomes too large

Solution:

# Use rotating capture files
tshark -i eth0 -b filesize:100000 -b files:5 -w capture

# Limit capture duration
timeout 300 tshark -i eth0 -w capture.pcap
Issue 4: No Traffic Visible
Problem: Wireshark captures no packets

Solution:

# Check interface is up
ip link show eth0

# Generate test traffic
ping -c 5 8.8.8.8

# Check if interface is in promiscuous mode
ip link show eth0 | grep PROMISC
